===Other spellings===
*[[deein]]
===Etymology===
''Dyin'' was loaned into English as '''[[gin#Etymology 3|gin]]'''.
===Noun===
'''dyin'''

# [[woman]]
===Quotations===
*'''1793''', [[w:Watkin Tench|Watkin Tench]], ''A Complete Account of the Settlement at Port Jackson''
*:“Oh,” said he, “she is become the wife of Colbee! But I have got ‘bulla muree '''deein'''’ (two large women) to compensate for her loss.”
